        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 11 at 4:17PM MDT by NWS Grand Junction CO</headline>
        <description>At 417 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 9
miles northeast of Snowmass, or 27 miles east of Glenwood Springs,
moving southeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 45 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Meridith.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
